    <div id="content-body">
    
        <h1 class="heading">Tools For LongURL</h1>

        <p class="center"><img src="http://assets.longurl.org/static/images/screenshot.png?1271277480" alt="LongURL Mobile Expander Screenshot" width="566" height="124" /></p>

        <p>Like the idea of LongURL but don't want to wait around for website developers to start using its API? Well you don't have to, not with the LongURL Mobile Expander. The LongURL Mobile Expander lets you expand shortened URLs on any website, no matter where you go! You can install it as either a <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/8636">Firefox extension</a> or <a href="http://userscripts.org/scripts/show/32115">Greasemonkey script</a>. Enjoy!</p>

        <link rel="commands" href="http://longurl.org/static/ubiquity.js" name="" />
        <p>Also, for you extra hip users, if you use the <a href="http://labs.mozilla.com/2008/08/introducing-ubiquity/">Ubiquity</a> extension for Firefox you can subscribe to the <code>expand-short-url</code> command from this page.</p>

        <p>If you are a site owner you can easily add LongURL support using a jQuery plugin. Check out the <a href="http://longurl.org/static/jquery_demo.html">demo</a>, and get the plugin from the <a href="http://plugins.jquery.com/project/longurl">jQuery plugin repository</a>.</p>
        
    </div><!-- close #content-body --></div>
